PN,31501
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1773176767
OL,3,CBlood test predicts dementia risk in
OL,4,Cwomen 'decades before symptoms appear'
OL,6,FA blood test can predict the risk of
OL,7,Fdementia in women up to 25 years
OL,8,Fbefore symptoms appear, according to
OL,9,Fresearchers.
OL,11,FExperts in the US have found that
OL,12,Fhigher levels of a protein called p-
OL,13,Ftau217, which is linked to the brain
OL,14,Fchanges seen in Alzheimer's disease,
OL,15,Fwere an accurate predictor of people
OL,16,Fdeveloping cognitive problems and
OL,17,Fdementia.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1773176767
OL,3,CBlood test predicts dementia risk in
OL,4,Cwomen 'decades before symptoms appear'
OL,6,FBritish researchers welcomed the study
OL,7,Fand said blood tests to pick up
OL,8,FAlzheimer's disease early were
OL,9,Fdeveloping at pace.
OL,11,FStatistics suggest women over 60 are
OL,12,Ftwice as likely to develop Alzheimer's
OL,13,Fdisease`the most common form of
OL,14,Fdementia`compared to men.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1773176767
OL,3,CBlood test predicts dementia risk in
OL,4,Cwomen 'decades before symptoms appear'
OL,6,FIn the new study, a team from the
OL,7,FUniversity of California San Diego
OL,8,Fexamined data for 2,766 women in the
OL,9,FWomen's Health Initiative Memory
OL,10,FStudy, a large US study that enrolled
OL,11,Fwomen aged 65 to 79 in the late 1990s
OL,12,Fand followed them for up to 25 years.
OL,14,FNone of those involved had any signs
OL,15,Fof cognitive impairment at the start
OL,16,Fof the study.
OL,18,FBlood samples collected at the start
OL,19,Fwere analysed, and then analysed again
OL,20,Fyears later to measure p-tau217.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1773176767
OL,3,CBlood test predicts dementia risk in
OL,4,Cwomen 'decades before symptoms appear'
OL,6,FDr Aladdin Shadyab, first author on
OL,7,Fthe study, said: "Our study suggests
OL,8,Fwe may be able to identify women at
OL,9,Felevated risk for dementia decades
OL,10,Fbefore symptoms emerge.
OL,12,F"That kind of long lead time opens the
OL,13,Fdoor to earlier prevention strategies
OL,14,Fand more targeted monitoring, rather
OL,15,Fthan waiting until memory problems are
OL,16,Falready affecting daily life.
OL,18,F"Ultimately, the goal is not just
OL,19,Fprediction, but using that knowledge
OL,20,Fto delay or prevent dementia
OL,21,Faltogether."
OL,26,@oD@ROUtD@AOUzD@AOU}D@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
